<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[324,404,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1982,2007]" captionTargetBox="[182,1371,668,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[162,1426,597,1963]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Ptychoptera lucida sp. nov. a. Habitus of male, lateral view, scale bar = 2.0 mm; b. Thorax, dorsal view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; c. Wing, scale bar = 1.0 mm; d. Female terminalia, lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356346/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 7a</figureCitation>
). Terga brownish black with posterior margins of 3rd to 5th terga pale. Sterna brownish black with posterior margins of 3rd to 7th sterna pale. Hairs on abdomen pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[377,444,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) brownish black. Epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[789,871,225,252]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8b</figureCitation>
) bilobed, lobes broad and swollen laterally with a quadrate projection on caudal area bearing dense short hairs; surstylus digitiform and broad basally with short hairs, curved inwards at middle, base with a Y-shaped lobe; proctiger bare medially, clothed with dense long hairs on posterior margin. Gonocoxite (
<figureCitation box="[498,578,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8c</figureCitation>
) short and stout with several short hairs laterally, 1.6 times as long as wide; basal apodeme 1/3 as long as gonocoxite; paramere with two pair of projections, outer projection slender, inner projection hook-shaped. Gonostylus (
<figureCitation box="[532,610,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8c</figureCitation>
) comprised of the following projections and lobes: a small S-shaped basal projection on inner side with short hairs; a large basal projection on dorsal side, broad at base with a small papillate projection, tapered and curved to the middle; a duckbilled lobe on middle area; an apical projection digitiform, rounded apically, with short hairs. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[697,778,513,540]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8d</figureCitation>
) triangular, broad basally, anterior margin concaved medially; base with several lateral hairs; middle with a wide membranous region; apex with two papillate projections, dorsal papillate projection with several long hairs. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[846,912,585,612]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,232,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[165,1422,166,1948]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ptychoptera lucidasp. nov. a. Male genitalia, lateral view; b.Epandrium, dorsal view; c. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view; d. Hypandrium, ventral view; e. Aedeagus, anterior view; f. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356348/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
e–f): subapical sclerite tongue-shaped, apex of subapical sclerite round.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,657,683]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 8.5–9.0 mm, wing length 8.5–9.0 mm. Similar to male. Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1284,657,684]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1982,2007]" captionTargetBox="[182,1371,668,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[162,1426,597,1963]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Ptychoptera lucida sp. nov. a. Habitus of male, lateral view, scale bar = 2.0 mm; b. Thorax, dorsal view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; c. Wing, scale bar = 1.0 mm; d. Female terminalia, lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3356346/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Fig. 7d</figureCitation>
): 8th sternum brown and swollen ventrally at middle, 2.5 times as long as 7th sternum; cercus brown, blade-shaped, 10th tergum + cercus 1.2 times as long as 8th sternum.
</paragraph>
