</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,152,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,909,935]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1818" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1818" box="[775,1082,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis box="[775,920,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">P. scutellaris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meigen, J. W." box="[927,1082,909,935]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468" refId="ref9783" refString="Meigen, J. W. (1818) Systematische Beschreibung der bekannten europaischen zweiflugeligen Insekten. Aachen, 1, i-xxxvi, 333 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 1373 1" type="book" year="1818">Meigen, 1818</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Europe, but it can be easily separated from the latter by the femora and tibiae mostly yellow and the surstylus curved toward median. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">P. scutellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the femora and tibiae are mostly blackish brown and the surstylus is straight. The new species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Tjeder, 1968" authorityName="Tjeder" authorityYear="1968" box="[264,503,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hugoi">
<emphasis box="[264,355,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">P. hugoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tjeder, B." box="[361,503,1017,1043]" pageId="13" pageNumber="468" pagination="73 - 79" refId="ref9911" refString="Tjeder, B. (1968) Notes on the Scandinavian Ptychopteridae, with description of a new species (Diptera). Opuscula Entomologica, 33, 73 - 79." type="journal article" year="1968">Tjeder, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Europe and 
<collectingCountry box="[705,817,1017,1043]" name="Mongolia" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
, but it can be separated from the latter by the wing with four weak brown clouds and one indistinct brown band and the inner projection of paramere hook-shaped. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tjeder" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hugoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="468">P. hugoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the wings have weak infuscation and the inner projection of paramere is straight.
</paragraph>
